MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: apps/client/src/shells/pulse/.*\.(tsx|ts)$
MATCH_CONTENT: document\.startViewTransition
ADVISORY: |
  Pulse already has a `runViewTransition` helper at
  `apps/client/src/shells/pulse/viewTransitions.ts`. Use it instead of
  calling `document.startViewTransition` directly.

  The helper:
    - Feature-detects VT support (Chromium only as of early 2026)
    - Respects `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` (runs the callback synchronously
      instead of forcing a morph on users who opted out)
    - Returns `transition.finished` wrapped in a catch so skipped transitions
      don't throw
    - Keeps the shell's VT usage consistent (ConfessionBooth, PulseBar, DmHero,
      CartridgeOverlay all use it)

  Replace:
    document.startViewTransition(() => dismiss())

  With:
    import { runViewTransition } from '../../viewTransitions';
    runViewTransition(() => dismiss());

  Naming namespace for `viewTransitionName` (keep tags unique):
    - `flying-tape`, `active-pill`, `pill-${cartridgeId}`, `chip-${playerId}`
    - `elim-portrait-${playerId}`, `winner-portrait-${playerId}` (reveals)
